SES
=====
https://aws.amazon.com/ses/pricing/

You can send 2,000 messages per day for free if you use Amazon SES from Amazon EC2 (or via AWS Elastic Beanstalk).
After 2,000 messages, you will be charged the current Amazon SES rate of $0.10 per thousand messages.
Attachment charges still apply, which are currently $0.12 per GB.

https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ses/latest/DeveloperGuide/send-using-sdk-java.html
https://www.rajith.me/2020/02/send-emails-using-aws-simple-email.html
https://www.tothenew.com/blog/aws-ses-integration-for-java-applications/
https://stackabuse.com/how-to-send-emails-in-java#sendingemailwithanattachment

